---
// Programmer's Curation Checklist — parallel to the Writers' Room Checklist
// and Funder's Slate Audit. For festival programmers, syllabus designers,
// and policy researchers building a curated body of films around a theme.
---
<div class="panel p-6 md:p-10 print:bg-white print:text-black">
  <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-gold-400">Programmer's Curation Checklist</p>
  <h3 class="mt-1 font-display text-2xl text-white">
    10 questions to ask of a curated lineup.
  </h3>
  <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-white/60 max-w-2xl">
    Whether you're locking a festival program, designing a film-studies
    syllabus, or assembling a policy brief grounded in screen examples, the
    line-up itself is an argument. This checklist surfaces what a lineup is
    implicitly saying about who, where, and how — so you can make those
    choices on purpose.
  </p>

  <ol class="mt-8 grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">01.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">What is the question this lineup is making the audience ask? State it in one sentence.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">02.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">If you mapped each film by its dominant emotion (shame / pride) and target gender, what shape does the program have?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">03.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Which films treat their central theme in a way that <em>reinforces</em> the dominant cultural pattern, and which complicate it?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">04.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Have you included at least one film that breaks the modal treatment of the program's central theme?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">05.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Whose voice is over-represented across the lineup? Whose is missing?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">06.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">If the lineup spans cultures, where does it show convergence (themes both sides share) and where does it show divergence?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">07.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">For films that depict shame around victimhood, are they paired with reading / discussion material that names the dynamic?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">08.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">If a viewer left after seeing only the first three films, what would they conclude is "normal"?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">09.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">What discussion prompt would help your audience name the norm a film is invoking, without telling them what to think about it?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">10.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">If you could add or replace one film to sharpen the lineup's argument, which would it be?</span>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 text-xs text-white/40">
    <button onclick="window.print()" class="rounded-full bg-white/5 px-4 py-2 text-white/70 ring-1 ring-white/10 hover:bg-white/10 hover:text-white transition print:hidden">
      Print this checklist
    </button>
    <span>or screenshot — it's CC-BY.</span>
  </div>
</div>
